---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Tools | Kreativ Sound"
  description="The Kreativ Sound tools area is currently a work in progress. Preset Mutator is the first upcoming browser tool and is marked as coming soon."
  canonical="https://kreativsound.com/tools/"
  activeNav="tools"
>
  <section class="card page-main product-page">
    <div class="stack">
      <div class="tools-hero">
        <p class="product-kicker">Work in progress</p>
        <h1 class="page-title">Browser tools are currently in development.</h1>
        <p class="page-lead">The Kreativ Sound tools area is being rebuilt. Preset Mutator is the first upcoming browser tool, with more experiments planned later.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="product-panel-grid product-tool-grid product-tool-grid-single">
        <section class="product-panel product-tool-card product-tool-card-coming-soon">
          <span class="product-tool-flow">Preset -&gt; Preset</span>
          <img class="product-tool-mark" src="/apps/presetmutator/ui/favicon.svg" width="128" height="128" alt="Preset Mutator logo" />
          <h2>Preset Mutator</h2>
          <p>Load one Vital preset, bias the mutation, and push it into new preset directions without leaving the browser.</p>
          <p class="product-tool-supporting">The first public tool release is being prepared now.</p>
          <div class="product-actions">
            <span class="button secondary is-static">
              <i class="fa-solid fa-hourglass-half" aria-hidden="true"></i>
              Coming soon
            </span>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>

      <section class="product-panel product-panel-summary">
        <h2>Current tools status</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>The public tools area is being repositioned and is not being promoted as a finished suite.</li>
          <li>Preset Mutator is the current focus and the next announced browser tool.</li>
          <li>More audio and preset utilities may return later once the direction is tighter.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
